@FeedingNys @LibertyCocaCola @NYSecofState @NYSDOS Continuamos coordinando el apoyo de organizaciones con sede en Nueva York para Puerto Rico.

Ayer, llegaron a la isla casi 37,000 libras de productos de @FeedingNys y 4,400 libras de agua de @LibertyCocaCola.

Nueva York siempre dará un paso al frente en tiempos de necesidad.

New York is ready to help our neighbors however and wherever they need us.

As we monitor #HurricaneIan, we continue to support our neighbors in Puerto Rico.

@NYGov is on the island supporting relief efforts and determining how we can further help with #HurricaneFiona recovery. https://t.co/vF4zcEwxst

We're making it easier for New Yorkers to get their polio vaccine if they haven't already received it.

@HealthNYGov is ramping up its vaccination efforts and EMTs, midwives, and pharmacists are now able to provide the vaccine.

Learn more: https://t.co/HKRa2Xgo2Y

State agencies are ready to help: 

@NYSDHSES is monitoring weather conditions &amp; coordinating response.

@NYSDPS is working with utilities to ensure they prepare for extreme heat.

@NYSDEC is monitoring air quality and is prepared to issue Air Quality Health Advisories if needed.

In New York, local health departments are currently distributing 28,093 doses of the monkeypox vaccine.

We know at-risk New Yorkers need vaccines, so we're fighting every day to get more doses quickly.

@HealthNYGov has lots of info to keep you safe &amp; informed. Learn more ⬇️ https://t.co/MCrfUiguRf

We're tracking severe thunderstorms across the state today, bringing threats of high winds, hail, &amp; flash flooding.

@NYGov agencies are ready to respond and to support communities as needed.

Keep a close eye on your local forecasts and stay safe! https://t.co/3V75qTULOq

Racist messages &amp; slurs were found in the Bronx &amp; Niagara today. 

@nyspolice is on alert in the wake of the Buffalo shooting &amp; is investigating both cases. We stand united against hate.

If you see or experience hate or bias, report it as soon as you can: https://t.co/qUI0p3fFHE

My heart is with the loved ones of the two New Yorkers lost in today's @mercyflightwny helicopter crash in Genesee County.
 
Their dedication and commitment to helping others will never be forgotten. 
@nyspolice are on the scene and continuing to investigate.

New York is leading the way toward a greener and cleaner future. #EarthWeek🌎

With our $500 million investment, we are making New York the nation’s hub for offshore wind💨

@Doreen_M_Harris of @NYSERDA explains how we’re making this goal a reality⤵️ https://t.co/aAB2cWo7VG

If you or someone you know has been impacted by sexual assault, New York State is here for you. 

@nysovs funds 200+ victim assistance programs that provide crisis counseling, therapy, and much more. 
Learn more: https://t.co/QdYmLDilwR #SAAM2022 https://t.co/UnWt8wHNR5

It’s a historic day for New York’s clean energy future:
@NYSDPS has approved two contracts to deliver renewable power to New York City!

These projects will create 10,000 high-quality jobs and are a major step forward on our path to reach a zero-emission grid by 2040.

To report an outage: 
@NYSEandG customers: Call 800-572-1131 or visit Outage Central at https://t.co/XPNfXg1hWq
@CentralHudson customers: Call 800-527-2714, text OUT to 236483, or visit https://t.co/Qe5vDgbLr6

We’re expecting to see dangerously cold temperatures across the state tonight through Saturday. For the most current weather warnings, watches and advisories in your area, follow: 
@NWSNewYorkNY
@NWSBUFFALO
@NWSAlbany
@NWSBinghamton
@NYSDHSES
or visit https://t.co/W983qkfRgU.

The SALT cap is nothing less than double taxation on New Yorkers. Repealing it will put money in families’ pockets and boost our economy.

@NewYorkStateAG and I are taking this to the Supreme Court to continue fighting for New York taxpayers.

https://t.co/vU4x0wSk2a

We're expanding testing by utilizing facilities already equipped for it. Testing sites are coming to:
@SUNYPlattsburgh
